{"cursor":"4678","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n]] .]]\n\n'Elegance' is a synonym for [[beauty]] that has come to acquire the additional\nconnotations of unusual effectiveness and simplicity. It is frequently used as a\nstandard of tastefulness particularly in the areas of visual design, decoration,\nthe sciences, and the esthetics of mathematics. Elegant things exhibit refined\nand dignified propriety.\n","linknr":275,"url":"Elegance","recorded":1362555032,"links":23,"instances":["sociology","disambiguation","emotion"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Concepts in aesthetics"],"headings":["General concept","In philosophy of science","In mathematics","In engineering","In chemistry","In pharmacy","References","Further reading"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/44/Fr%C3%A9d%C3%A9ric_Soulacroix_-_Elegance_Of_The_Epoque.jpg/220px-Fr%C3%A9d%C3%A9ric_Soulacroix_-_Elegance_Of_The_Epoque.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9a/Pythagorean_proof_%281%29.svg/200px-Pythagorean_proof_%281%29.svg.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["taste","sociology"],["isomorphism","disambiguation"],["surprise","emotion"]],"members":["taste","isomorphism","surprise"],"related":["Synonym","Connotation","Effectiveness","Simplicity","Taste_(sociology)","Visual_design","Decorative_arts","Mathematical_beauty","Isomorphism_(disambiguation)","Douglas_Hofstadter","Simplicity","Consistency","Design","Essence","Color","Philosophy_of_science","Simplicity","Ontological_simplicity","Parsimony","Mathematical_proof","Mathematics","Theorem","Mathematical_elegance","Surprise_(emotion)","Computer_program","C